---
import StarlightPage from "@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro";
---

<StarlightPage
  frontmatter={{
    title: "Design",
    description: "Links into Warden's architectural decisions and long-form design notes.",
  }}
>
  <section class="design-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Architecture notes</p>
    <h2>The work is mostly choosing what <em>not</em> to build.</h2>
    <p>
      Warden has a public surface, but the real project is the discipline behind it: what gets
      verified, what stays local, what is deferred, and where the model is not allowed to improvise.
      These are the source documents for that discipline.
    </p>

    <div class="link-grid">
      <a href="https://github.com/99Yash/warden/blob/main/decisions.md" rel="noreferrer">
        <span>decisions.md</span>
        <strong>Architectural <em>Decisions</em></strong>
        <p>The choices, rejections, caveats, and milestone boundaries that keep scope honest.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/99Yash/warden/blob/main/vision.md" rel="noreferrer">
        <span>vision.md</span>
        <strong>Thinking <em>Framework</em></strong>
        <p>The original long-form argument for a reviewer that derives knowledge instead of assuming it.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/99Yash/warden/blob/main/CONTEXT.md" rel="noreferrer">
        <span>CONTEXT.md</span>
        <strong>Noun <em>Glossary</em></strong>
        <p>The shared vocabulary for comments, findings, citations, runners, and deferred surfaces.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</StarlightPage>

<style>
  .design-page h2 em,
  .link-grid strong em {
    font-family: var(--warden-font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--warden-orange);
  }
</style>
